Exercises
Q1. A source: v(t) = 311×sin(314t + 45°) V.
(a) Find V_m, V_rms, f, T, ω, φ
(b) Find v at t = 5ms
(c) Find the first time t > 0 when v = 200V
(d) A second source: v2(t) = 200×sin(314t − 30°). Add using phasors. Give result in polar and time domain form.
Q2. RMS calculations — mixed waveforms:
(a) Sinusoid: V_m = 170V. Find V_rms.
(b) PWM: 24V amplitude, D = 0.35. Find V_rms.
(c) PWM: 12V amplitude, D = 0.75. Find V_rms.
(d) Triangular wave: peaks at ±15V. Find V_rms.
(e) A waveform that is 0V for half the period and a sinusoid of amplitude 10V for the other half. Explain why V_rms ≠ 10/√2.
Q3. Series RC circuit: R = 100Ω, C = 50µF, source = 230V RMS at 50Hz.
(a) Z_C at 50Hz
(b) Z_total magnitude and phase angle
(c) RMS current
(d) V_R and V_C (RMS)
(e) Does current lead or lag voltage? By how much?
(f) At what frequency does |Z_C| = R? What is the significance of this frequency?
Q4. Series RLC: R = 10Ω, L = 50mH, C = 200µF.
(a) Resonant frequency f_r
(b) At f_r: find Z_total. What is special about it?
(c) At f_r with V_source = 50V RMS: find current, V_R, V_L, V_C
(d) At 10Hz below resonance: is the circuit inductive or capacitive?
(e) At 10Hz above resonance: is it inductive or capacitive?
Q5. A single-phase solar inverter produces 230V RMS at 50Hz from a 400V DC bus.
(a) Peak AC voltage required
(b) Modulation index m = V_peak_AC / V_DC. Why must m ≤ 1?
(c) Battery discharges and DC bus drops to 320V. Can 230V RMS still be produced? Show numerically.
(d) Minimum DC bus voltage for 230V RMS output with m = 0.95
